fr.gouv.finances.dgfip.xemelios.data

Interface DataImpl

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataImpl, PdfDataLayer

    public interface DataImpl
    Defines what a data implementation must implement Implementations must provide a constructor with a PropertiesExpansion parameter.

                                              int level,

        For a given document model, returns the parent collectivites of level level, that matches eventualsotherParents, this user is allowed to search in.
        If otherParents is null or empty, returns all parent collectivites of required level.
        If otherParents is not empty, otherParents[0] will be used to match level+1 parent, otherParents[1] will be used to match level+2 parent, and so on...
        Parameters:
        dm - The document to search for
        level - The level of parent collectivite to find. level must be >=1
        otherParents - The eventuals parents the returned parents must match
        user - The user that is performing the search
        Returns:
        Throws:
        DataConfigurationException
        DataAccessException
        UnauthorizedException
